quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,103,"And indeed We know that they say, “This Qur’an is being taught by some other man”; the one they refer to speaks a foreign language, whereas this is clear Arabic!"
  16,104,"Those who disbelieve in the signs of Allah – Allah does not guide them, and for them is a punishment, most painful."
  16,105,"Only those who do not believe in Allah’s signs attribute lies and fabrications; and they themselves are liars."
  16,106,"The one who disbelieves in Allah after accepting faith – except him who is forced to and whose heart is still firmly upon faith – but whoever is wholeheartedly a disbeliever, upon them is the wrath of Allah; and for them is a great punishment."
  16,107,"This is because the worldly life was dearer to them than the Hereafter; and because Allah does not guide such disbelieving people."
  16,108,"These are the ones whose hearts, ears, and eyes Allah has sealed; and they are the neglectful."
  16,109,"So it occurred that they are the losers in the Hereafter."
  16,110,"Then indeed your Lord – for those who migrated after they had been oppressed, and then fought and remained patient – indeed your Lord is then, surely, Oft Forgiving, Most Merciful."
